<br>
It's the type of post where you need to INCLUDE other classes to make it so your fair and biased and not to whine and to be polite. <br>
<br>
<br>
Before I go into some of my suggestions I want to go into some of the statements out there that are either confusing, not defined or just plain not true. <br>
<br>
1) The definition of a light tank (regardless of realm) is to produce more Offensive damage then that realm's main tank, with the disadvantage of having less defense then that realm's main tank. <br>
<br>
Now currently (pre 1.62) this does not hold true for Mercs/BM's. and then after the reduction to LA damage output it does not Hold true for all 3 classes (mercs/bms/zerkers) <br>
<br>
2. Zerkers still win more often then not when fighting a main tank. This is simply not true. There have been tons of logs/tests on vn pendragon and vn viking boards that proves this does not hold true. <br>
<br>
3. Zerkers can 2 shot tanks all the time. I have not yet to date seen any proof of this is a controlled environment that shows the data that it was a legit fight and not something that was faked where the person had no armor on sitting down and the person was hit from behind. Screenshots can be easily produced to show such results. Now in the same breath it may happen in a very rare possibility type of form because anything is possible if you hit all the right combinations. But to say this is the norm is not true. <br>
<br>
4. Zerkers Own the Battlefield. Now when i read this i did smile at it... not in a pride sort of way but more as a joke. It's fairly safe to say no tank (light or heavy) own the battlefield. Casters do. they have the ability to lay down the nuke power that just levels out groups of tanks that have to cross the range they hold. Now it is true that if we do get into range of them we will surely kill them. But that's the balance of the game, melee range vs caster range. but zerkers do not own the battlefield. <br>
<br>
5. RVR should be balance realm vs realm not class vs class or 1 on 1. RVR is not fought 1 on 1 in nice control environments. the whole realm can effect how much damage you output onto someone else. there are way to many variables to say that a growth rate is the only thing that says LA is overpowered. <br>
<br>
6. The problem was stated that LA + End regen was the problem. thus saying there was no problem with the 2 separate. So why are both being adjusted so harshly? Does this not penalize the players that do not have a buffing partner around all the time or when they are just plain solo or when their buffer dies? I'm confused on how both are to be adjusted when separate they are fine? <br>
<br>
7. The fixing of the Block/Parry bug. Now that this is fixed does that not mean that players will have more opportunity to block/parry attacks thus making it harder to get hit. How can a reduction to a style line be put in the same time more defensive abilities are put in? Thus saying are you sure you need to reduce the amount we are hitting for by so much if people can defend better now...? <br>
<br>
8. Shadowblades and Zerkers both use the LA style line. making changes can hurt both classes in different ways. I'm sure by now that the technology is there to make changes to one class and not effect the other? Thus saying the SB's are getting hit hard since they can not fully spec through out 5 spec lines were as Zerkers have 3. <br>
<br>
<br>
Suggested fixes: <br>
<br>
<br>
1) 10-15% reduction to LA from pre-1.62. Currently in 1.62 there is a 30-40% reduction in damage output. This is simply to harsh to fast. Plus the problem that was stated was when End regen was combined with LA. If both are to be reduced please reconsider how much they are being reduced when combined vs when not combined. the effects are vastly different. <br>
<br>
2) Merc/BM lines should be buffed up to equivalent damage of the 10-15% reduction LA, but LA should have a slight damage advantage. I believe Mythic has stated in the past that LA was a slightly more deadly line style then it's sister classes. <br>
<br>
3. All light tanks should have more Offensive damage output then their realms main tanks, but have less Defensive output then their realms main tanks. (as per the class description which is now not true for all realm's light tanks) adjust number 1 and 2 accordingly to actually make this description work. <br>
<br>
4. Frenzy should have the negatives removed from it since now all light tanks abilities are on a 7 minute time with just positive effects (on merc/bm's) with no negatives. other suggestions would be make Frenzy immune to spell crits while in frenzy but keep the negatives. A change to this ability would be a welcome change. <br>
<br>
5. Level 50 LA style should be reversed back to work off an opponent's Parry... we never asked for a 3rd chain or a dd.. this was an unwanted change. Seeing how Parry/block have been fixed. If this can be reverse it will be greatly appreciated. <br>
<br>
6. Make different Line styles for both SB's and Zerkers. It is obvious the technology is there. No need to reduction both classes because they use the same style lines. <br>
