<br>
Light Tank Offense vs. Defense:<br>
<br>
I think you make some fair points, but I think Zerker defense is where it should be.  Shields make a huge difference (and will be even more powerful once 1.62 is implemented).  Many main tanks opt to spec offensively forgoing the defensive route offered by a high Shield spec.  When they do that, then arguably, their defensive skills are not as great as a Berserker's (Evade 3, studded and solid Parry vs. Evade 1, solid Parry and chain), but that's not really our problem.  That's a choice they've made.  I think this is less true of Mercs and Shieldmasters and perhaps a downward adjustment should be made defensively with respect to those classes (though only if their is an offensive upgrade to those classes).<br>
<br>
Aurora Borealis:<br>
<br>
I agree that it should not sit at the end of a 3 style chain, but I would prefer to see it serve as a side positional style.  I would also like to see the bleed on Snowsquall significantly enhanced (I actually believe all style bleeds should be increased) to something like 25 - 20 - 15 - 10 - 5.<br>
<br>
That's it.  Nice email Hord. <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 5.7 Berserker - Palo<br>
Hammer Tyme - 50th RR 3.2 Skald - Palo<br>
Syf Stormcrow - 50th RR 3.5 Huntress - Palo<br>
Grimrr - 32nd Savage - Palo<br>
