<br>
You love the concept of dual-wielding, that's great. So do we all, and we know that speccing in shield not only means being inferior to a Warrior/Hero/Armsman/Paladin/Reaver but it also means wasting offensive spec points and there's the hotkey shield issue meaning dual-wielding calsses can't effectively swap shields and offhand weapons easily (at all).<br>
<br>
So most mercs/BMs don't spec shield. Maybe they spec 7 in Shield for the first Guard or something to do during a keep siege, but thats hardly a boon to the calss. I know one dude specced 23 Shield, but I'm sure he knew what he was doing. I personally wouldn't ever do that. The reason people spec shield is for the anytime stun- at spec 42.<br>
<br>
Whereupon they pull out their pole/CS/2H, or just keep chanting and hitting. Dual Wielding classes don't spec 42 shield because that means being a complete gimp with inferior armour, shield and no damage improvement really after the slam has taken effect.<br>
<br>
Saying Mercenaries and Blademasters need a defensive tone-down and that berzerkers need a tone-up is not, in my mind, logical.<br>
<br>
If you're not asking for shield spec, why not have it anyway. Instead of asking for something else.<br>
<br>
On the armour issue, yeah most Albion tanks go Slash, and will get a bonus against you. And BladeMasters wear Studded and are slash-resistant, and mercenaries wear Midgard-chain except not slash-resistant, without being able to use Shield Slam AND hit for 140% base damage when the opponent is stunned.<br>
<br>
Bringing shield and armour type into the light tank equation gives you a mess. Either ask for it, or don't ask for it, but don't say we've got medium shield option and so we're superior.<br>
<br>
You're more than welcome to ask for Flurry, too.<br>
<br>
My apoligies if this post sounds a bit rude, but your thoughts on potantial defense versus offensive damage output just seemed bad.<br>
<br>
