left axe = style damage<br>
<br>
At least thats what I remember. I think.. a bit rusting on some things.<br>
<br>
So yes lowering either of them does lower your damage output but even more in Left axe... why because the growth rate is what you take advantage of to give you that boost to your over all damage that is produced from style bonus. Since the growth rate is far less and then you lessen how much of that growth rate you get... the difference from your pre 1.62 damage and your new 1.62 damage is far greater.<br>
<br>
If i had to choose from the 2 i would lessen axe first.<br>
<br>
But then again I think the 50 50 28 spec is perfectly fine. Then again i have +15 to my skills and mastery of parry 1 that gives me pretty damn close to a 50 in parry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
As for the shield spec in the BM line. I have no clue why mythic gave that to you guys. I don't know their reasoning behind it. Obviously they must know of some spec that no-one has ever come across. <br>
<br>
As for armor I'm pretty sure studded isn't slash resistant... It's vulnerable to slash. Chain is vulnerable to thrust. I'd have to say 75% of every opponent out there uses Slash. it's the most used damage type in the game. So wearing armor that is medium range and then vulnerable to the most used damage type in the game is a huge negative to defense. It means your going to get hit more and harder.<br>
<br>
As for the special abilities of each class. Hey I like them being different. Do they need tweaked yeah... Bm/Mercs got some tweaks now they are on a 7 minute timer with positive effects and no negatives. Is it the best solution over all for your class, I have no idea i've never played a Merc/Bm do i think it's a good step in the right direction Yes... is it enough no.<br>
